<h1>Purpose</h1>
<p>Classify words depending on their function and grammatical behaviour in a sentence.</p>
<p>The following types of words are possible:</p>
<ul>
    <li><span class=LogicalConnectors>Logical Connectors:</span> terms like <i>additionally, for instance,</i> and <i>despite</i></li>
    <li><span class=RegulatoryOperators>Regulatory Operators:</span> </li>
    <li><span class=EconomicOperands>Economic Operands:</span> terms like <i>bailout, systemic risk</i> and <i>key role</i></li>
    <li><span class=Attributes>Attributes:</span> </li>
    <li><span class=LegalReferences>Legal References:</span> terms like <i>Affordable Housing Act (42 U.S.C. 12773(b)(2)), Securities Exchange Act of 1934</i> and <i>the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 (15 U.S.C. 7201 et seq.)</i></li>
    <li><span class=FunctionWords>Function Words:</span></li>
    <li><span class=Other>Other:</span></li>
</ul>


<h1>Features</h1>
<ul>
    <li>Highlighting of selected text: Select and pick the color for each word(s).</li>
    <li>Update and find the list of words: Store the list of words highlighted during your session and find them in the document.</li>
    <li>Remove words: Select and remove words already highlighted.</li>
    <li>Change title: Select different titles.</li>
    <li>Check the list  of words classified during your session.</li>
</ul>

<h1>How it works?</h1>
<ul>
    <li>Select the word. </li>
    <li>Right click. </li>
    <li>Choose the type of word or the task from the menu</li>
</ul>


